literals: "Prepare to have your fortune actually predicted.\nIf you'd like to quit, just type \"quit\" instead of an answer."
"\nFirst, please type your first name, then press enter."
"Great, how about your last name?"
"Now, not to get too personal, but how old are you?"
"You cannot be an amount of years old that is not a number.\nWe're going to say you're 10,000. Nice going, Methuselah."
"And if you could be born in any month you were actually born in, what would that month be?"
"\nYou can write the name or its number, but no abbreviations like Oct or Jan. May is alright."
"january"
"february"
"march"

"Did you misspell something? Let's just say you were born in February."
"Out of the ROY G. BIV colors, which is your favorite? If you don't know what these are, type HELP"
"HELP"
"You know, the ROG. B IVY Colors."
"I mean Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, Indigo, or Violet. That's who ROY G. BIV is."
"ROY G BIV stands for: Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, Indigo, Violet."
"Like, the R is for Red. O is Orange. And so on. Indigo is like, a purple kind of blue."
"You could say red. Or orange. Or yellow. Green is fine. As are blue and violet, aka purple.\nAlso acceptable is indigo. Please type one of these."
"Finally, how many siblings do you have?"
"The number of siblings you have should be a number. Let's just say there's 2 of them."

"adjacent to your normal home. What could be more practical? Saves so much gas."
"on the banks of Steverson Lake, Nebraska. It's not that bad, and you got a really good deal on the real estate.\nAnd nobody is ever asking to come visit you, so you get that solitude."
"a vast complex of linked hot air baloons, floating over Porcupine, South Dakota.\nYou've been designing this for years. They said you couldn't do it.\nBut you could."
"constantly in peril of being \"borrowed for the weekend\" by your siblings."
"in the Akmola Province of Kazakhstan. It beautiful and far, far away from your many, many siblings."
"in an underground bunker. Your army of siblings has tried to draft you into a weird militia.\nYou're on the run by this point. This is your only refuge."
"bank balance error"
"six dollars but the actual Mona Lisa in a safe deposit box in Switzerland."
"$125 for appearance's sake, but you actually keep your money in gold bars\nunder your mattress because the government."

"all the money in the world. All of it. Your super villain plan worked, but in the process\nyou obviously destabilized the economy and all that currency is worthless.\nThe bank laughs at you as they trade their livestock for grain on the bartering market."
"the secrets of the universe, considering you were born outside of time."

"an actual rocket ship. It's useless for going to Kroger, but not to get to Moon Kroger!"
"eight reindeer hitched together like you're motherfuckin' Santa Claus"
"a puma you've caught, trained, and made a cute little saddle for. It is fearsome."
"your own feet. You don't need any fancy automobile when you've got two cars on the end of your legs!"
"a submarine. The world has flooded by this point. The grocery store is in a kelp forest."

"an infinite number of brick masons who are constantly restructuring the built environment to move around you.\nYou don't go to the store. The store comes to you. All movement is an illusion, but yours is especially."
"a dog sled team, but instead of dogs it's norwegian forest cats and instead of a sled it's a surfboard.\nYou're pretty bodacious in your old age."
"equipped with six GPS devices but it doesn't matter becuase you don't follow directions anyway."
